title: Scott Morrison - Wikipedia
snippet: Scott John Morrison (born 13 May 1968) is an Australian former politician who served as the 30th prime minister of Australia from 2018 to 2022. title: Morrison government - Wikipedia
snippet: The Morrison government was the federal executive government of Australia, led by Prime Minister Scott Morrison of the Liberal Party of Australia, between 2018 and 2022. The Morrison government commenced on 24 August 2018, when it was sworn in by the Governor-General of Australia.

title: Scott Morrison | naa.gov.au
snippet: On 24 August 2018, Scott Morrison became Australia's 30th prime minister. Morrison was first elected to parliament as the federal member for Cook on 24 November 2007.
